Better active version: normalized form

Raw ratios can get weird, so use a balanced error metric too:

\Delta_G(x) = \frac{|Love(x) - Logic(x)|}{Love(x)+Logic(x)+\epsilon}

Where small \epsilon prevents divide-by-zero.

Then:
	•	0 = perfect balance
	•	closer to 0 = better
	•	larger value = distortion

This gives you two useful outputs:
	•	G(x) = direction of imbalance
	•	ΔG(x) = magnitude of imbalance

So:
	•	G(x) tells you which side is overweight
	•	\Delta_G(x) tells you how bad it is

