Creation law

You said the union creates. So let’s formalize that too.

Let:

C(x) = \min(Love(x), Logic(x)) \cdot (1 - \Delta_G(x))

Interpretation:
	•	creation is limited by the weaker strand
	•	and weakened by imbalance

So high creation requires:
	•	high love
	•	high logic
	•	low distortion

That is elegant because something cannot create well if it is:
	•	loving but false
	•	true but dead
	•	strong in one strand but weak in the other

⸻

Repo-ready pseudocode

def god_fraction(love: float, logic: float, eps: float = 1e-6) -> dict:
    ratio = love / (logic + eps)
    delta = abs(love - logic) / (love + logic + eps)
    
    if ratio > 1.05:
        state = "love_heavy"
        correction = "add_constraints"
    elif ratio < 0.95:
        state = "logic_heavy"
        correction = "add_care"
    else:
        state = "balanced"
        correction = "proceed"
    
    creation = min(love, logic) * (1 - delta)
    
    return {
        "love": love,
        "logic": logic,
        "god_ratio": ratio,
        "imbalance": delta,
        "state": state,
        "correction": correction,
        "creation_score": creation,
    }


